Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 9. Remove the @Puff Pastry Sheet{1/2%pack} from your fridge and allow to come up to room temperature.

Pop the @Garlic Clove{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{some} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel on a #baking tray{} until soft, ~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice the @Onion{1}.

Heat another large saucepan with a tight-fitting #lid{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}.

Once the onions are soft, add the @Slow Cooked Beef{280%g} along with the juices from the packet. Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a #fork{}, ~{10-15%mins}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%mins}.

Once the beef is tender, remove the lid and shred the beef with two #forks{}. Stir through the @Teriyaki Sauce{100%g} and season with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}. Add a splash of @water{some} if you feel it needs it, then remove from the heat. Transfer the beef mixture into an appropriately sized #baking dish{}. Wipe out the saucepan for later.

Cover the beef filling with the pastry (see ingredients for amount), pressing it over the side of the dish or just sitting it on top, then trimming off any excess.

Make a small hole in the middle to allow steam to escape. TIP: Brush the pastry with a little @?milk{some} if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%mins}. Once it's out of the oven, allow the pie to stand for ~{2%mins}.

Meanwhile, once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pan{}, off the heat. Add the roasted garlic, a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{some} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{some} in the (now empty) saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%mins}, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%min}.

Add a splash of @water{some} and immediately cover with a lid or some foil. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once the beans are tender, remove from the heat. Stir through @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} and toss to coat.

Share your teriyaki beef pie between your #serving plates{}.

Serve with your roasted garlic mash and sesame green beans alongside. Enjoy!

> Keep any remaining pastry for another recipe!